{
  "texts": [
    "We also perform a regression study to fit a linear function t box = a • t point + b.",
    "The resulting coefficient of determination R 2 = 0.9824, demonstrating a strong linear correlation.While we do not position this as our contribution, we implement the support of querying box geometries for multidimensional learned indexes.",
    "This feature enables existing work to index more complex geometries, such as polygons, which is left for future work.",
    "By augmenting three datasets-Uniform, FourSquare, and OSM-we found that querying box geometries takes 1.73× to 2.19× longer than for point datasets.",
    "Notably, efficient indexes like Flood and IFI also perform well with box queries."
  ]
}